{[%mdl 8192] D34: Tarrasch Defence: 6 g3 Nf6 7 Bg2 Be7} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 e6 3.
Nc3 c5 4. cxd5 exd5 5. g3 Nc6 6. Nf3 Nf6 7. Bg2 Be7 8. O-O O-O 9. Re1 (9. a3 c4
10. Bg5 h6 11. Bxf6 Bxf6 12. e3 Be6 13. Nd2 Qd7 14. b3 cxb3 15. Nxb3 b6 16. Qe2
Rac8 17. Rfc1 Ne7 18. Qa6 Rfd8 19. Bf1 Nc6 20. Qa4 Rc7 21. Nd2 Na5 22. Qxd7
Rcxd7 23. Nb5 Be7 {Ikonnikov,V (2560)-Feygin,M (2529) Belgium 2010 1-0 (44)}) (
9. Na4 c4 10. b3 b5 11. Nc5 Bf5 12. Nh4 Bg4 13. Re1 Rc8 14. bxc4 dxc4 15. Bb2
Bxc5 16. dxc5 Qxd1 17. Rexd1 b4 18. Rd6 Ne7 19. Bd4 Ne8 20. Ra6 g5 21. Nf3 Nc7
22. Rf6 Ne6 23. Be3 Nd5 {Akdag,D (2218)-Kristensen,K (2296) Denmark 2011 0-1 
(38)}) 9... h6 $146 {Covers g5} (9... Re8 10. Bg5 cxd4 11. Nxd4 h6 12. Bf4 Bb4
13. Rc1 Bg4 14. a3 Ba5 15. Nxc6 bxc6 16. b4 Bb6 17. Na4 Qd7 18. Nc5 Bxc5 19.
Rxc5 Bh3 20. Qc2 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 Re6 22. b5 cxb5 23. Rc7 Qe8 24. Qd3 {Szoen,D 
(2450)-Zolnierowicz,K (2287) Warsaw 2005 1-0 (40)}) 10. Bf4 a6 {Prevents
intrusion on b5} 11. Rc1 c4 {Black has a very active position} 12. Ne5 Be6 13.
e4 Re8 14. h3 {Controls g4} (14. exd5 Nxd5 15. Bxd5 Bxd5 $16) 14... Bb4 (14...
Nxe5 $5 {is worth consideration} 15. dxe5 Nxe4 16. Nxe4 dxe4 17. Bxe4 Qb6 $11)
15. exd5 $14 {White forks: c6+e6} Nxd5 {A sound move.} 16. Nxc6 (16. Nxf7 Bxf7
17. Rxe8+ Qxe8 18. Nxd5 Rd8 19. Nxb4 Nxb4 20. Bxb7 Nxa2 $14) 16... bxc6 $11 17.
Bd2 Qa5 18. Re5 Rad8 19. Qh5 Bxc3 {Black forks: b2, d2+d4} 20. Rxc3 (20. bxc3
$5 {should be examined more closely} f6 21. Re4 $11) 20... Qxa2 $17 21. Rf3 $4
{another bit of territory lost} (21. Rc1 f6 (21... Qxb2 $143 22. Bxh6 f6 23.
Re4 $11) 22. Re4 Bf7 $17 (22... Qxb2 $6 23. Bxh6 Qb7 24. Bd2 $15)) 21... Qb1+ (
21... f6 $142 {seems even better} 22. Rxe6 Rxe6 23. Bc3 $19) 22. Kh2 (22. Re1
$142 Qc2 23. Ba5 $17) 22... Qg6 $4 {releasing the pressure on the opponent} (
22... f6 $142 {the advantage is on the side of Black} 23. Re1 Qxb2 24. Bxh6 Qc2
$19 (24... gxh6 $6 25. Qg6+ Kh8 26. Qxh6+ Kg8 27. Qg6+ Kf8 28. Rxf6+ Nxf6 29.
Qxf6+ Bf7 30. Qh8+ Bg8 31. Qf6+ Bf7 32. Qh8+ Bg8 33. Qf6+ Bf7 $11)) 23. Qxg6
$11 fxg6 {Black has new doubled pawns: g6+g7} 24. Ra3 Bc8 25. Rxe8+ Rxe8 26.
Bf1 {White threatens to win material: Bf1xc4} Re4 27. Bc3 Nxc3 28. bxc3 {
Black has a new passed pawn: a6.} Be6 29. h4 Bd5 30. Rxa6 Re1 31. Bg2 Rc1 {
Black threatens to win material: Rc1xc3} 32. Ra3 Kf7 33. Bxd5+ cxd5 {A rook
endgame occured} 34. Kg2 Rb1 35. Ra2 Rc1 36. Ra3 1/2-1/2

