b3 (3. e3 b6 4. Nf3 Bb7 5. Be2 c5 6. O-O Be7 7. b3 O-O 8. Bb2 d6 9. d4 cxd4 10.
Nxd4 a6 11. Bf3 Qc7 12. Bxb7 Qxb7 13. Qf3 Qxf3 14. Nxf3 Nbd7 15. Rfd1 Rfd8 16.
Ba3 Nc5 17. Bxc5 bxc5 {Granados Gomez,M (2388)-Matnadze,A (2395) Barcelona
2015 1/2-1/2 (54)}) 3... c6 $146 {Consolidates b5+d5} (3... d5 4. e3 (4. Nf3 d4
5. Nb5 c5 6. d3 a6 7. Na3 Nc6 8. g3 Bd6 9. Bg2 O-O 10. Nc2 h6 11. O-O e5 12. a3
Re8 13. e4 dxe3 14. Bxe3 Bf5 15. Nh4 Bh7 16. Re1 Bf8 17. Bf1 Qd7 18. Qd2 Rad8 {
Simunek,A (2198)-Blazek,J (2197) Czechia 2007 0-1 (38)}) 4... c5 5. Nf3 (5.
cxd5 exd5 6. d4 Qa5 7. Bb2 Nc6 8. dxc5 Bxc5 9. a3 d4 10. b4 Bxb4 11. axb4 Qxb4
12. Qd2 dxc3 13. Bxc3 Qe7 14. Bd3 Ne4 15. Bxe4 Qxe4 16. Ne2 O-O 17. O-O Be6 18.
Qb2 Qg4 19. h3 Qg5 {Momeni,E (2263)-Sadeh,S (2200) Teheran 2008 1/2-1/2 (42)})
5... d4 6. exd4 cxd4 7. Ne2 Nc6 8. d3 e5 9. a3 a5 10. Ng3 Be7 11. Be2 O-O 12.
O-O Rb8 13. Ne1 b5 14. f4 bxc4 15. bxc4 Bd6 16. f5 e4 17. Nxe4 Nxe4 18. dxe4 {
Sliwa,B (2200)-Adamski,J (2415) Augustow 1975 1/2-1/2 (31)}) (3... Nc6 4. Nf3
$11) 4. Bb2 d5 5. e3 Nbd7 6. d4 Bd6 7. Bd3 O-O 8. Nge2 Qc7 (8... e5 9. h3 $11)
9. h3 {Secures g4} h6 10. O-O b6 11. Rc1 Bb7 12. Bb1 (12. cxd5 Nxd5 13. Nb5
Bh2+ 14. Kh1 Qb8 $11) 12... Rad8 (12... a6 13. cxd5 exd5 14. g3 $11) 13. Qd3 (
13. cxd5 exd5 14. Nb5 Qb8 15. Nxd6 Qxd6 $14) 13... Rfe8 (13... dxc4 14. Qxc4 c5
15. Rfd1 $11) 14. e4 (14. cxd5 $142 exd5 15. Nb5 $14) 14... e5 $4 {Black has
let it slip away} (14... dxe4 $142 {would keep Black alive} 15. Nxe4 Nxe4 16.
Qxe4 Nf6 $15) 15. cxd5 $16 exd4 16. Nxd4 (16. Nb5 $5 Bh2+ 17. Kh1 $16) 16...
Nc5 $14 17. Qc2 Bf4 18. Rce1 cxd5 $2 (18... Be5 19. Nf3 Bxc3 20. Qxc3 cxd5 21.
exd5 $14) 19. exd5 $4 {White lets it slip away. .} (19. Nxd5 $142 {a pity that
White didn't try this} Bxd5 20. exd5 $18) 19... Ba6 {Black threatens to win
material: Ba6xf1} (19... Bh2+ 20. Kh1 Be5 21. Nf5 $14) 20. Ndb5 $16 {White
threatens to win material: Nb5xc7} Qd7 21. a4 g6 $2 (21... Be5 22. Rxe5 Rxe5
23. b4 Nxa4 24. Qxa4 Bxb5 25. Qxb5 Rxd5 26. Qc4 $16) 22. Rd1 $4 {forfeits the
advantage} (22. b4 Nb7 23. Qd3 Bxb5 24. axb5 $18 (24. Qxb5 $6 Qxb5 25. Nxb5
Rxe1 26. Rxe1 Nxd5 $14)) 22... Bg5 (22... Rc8 23. Rfe1 Be5 24. Rxe5 Rxe5 25. b4
Bxb5 26. bxc5 $14) 23. Rfe1 (23. Rd4 $142 Nh5 24. b4 $16) 23... Qb7 $4 {
[%cal Rb7d5,Rd8d5,Rf6d5,Gc3d5,Gd1d5] The pressure on the isolated pawn grows.
causes even greater problems} (23... Bb7 $142 24. Rxe8+ Qxe8 $16) 24. b4 $18
Ncd7 (24... Bxb5 25. bxc5 Rxe1+ 26. Rxe1 $18) 25. Rxe8+ (25. Nd6 $142 {might
be the shorter path} Rxe1+ 26. Rxe1 Qb8 27. Nxf7 Kxf7 28. Qxg6+ Kf8 $18) 25...
Nxe8 26. Ne4 Bxb5 27. axb5 a5 (27... Qc8 28. Qe2 Ndf6 29. Nxg5 hxg5 $18) 28.
Nxg5 hxg5 29. bxa5 bxa5 30. Qc3 Ndf6 31. Qxa5 Rxd5 32. Rxd5 Qxd5 33. Ba2 (33.
Bc2 $142 $5 {and White can already relax} Ne4 $18) 33... Qd1+ {[%cal Yg5g4]
Black plans g4} 34. Kh2 Qd6+ 35. g3 g4 $4 {the pressure is too much, Black
crumbles} (35... Qc5 36. Kg2 Ne4 37. Bxf7+ Kh7 $18) 36. Qa7 (36. b6 $142 {
keeps an even firmer grip} Qc6 37. Qa7 Nd7 38. hxg4 Qxb6 39. Qxd7 Qxf2+ 40. Kh3
Qf1+ 41. Kh4 Kf8 $18) 36... Nd5 (36... Qd7 {a fruitless try to alter the
course of the game} 37. b6 gxh3 38. Bb3 Ng4+ 39. Kxh3 Ne5+ 40. Qxd7 Nxd7 41. b7
$18) 37. Qa8 (37. Qd4 $142 {might be the shorter path} Ndf6 38. Qxd6 Nxd6 39.
Bxf6 Nxb5 40. hxg4 Nd6 $18) 37... Ndc7 38. Qe4 gxh3 (38... Ng7 {doesn't do any
good} 39. Be5 Qd2 40. Bxc7 Qxa2 41. b6 Qxf2+ 42. Qg2 $18) 39. Kxh3 (39. Be5 Qd7
40. b6 Na6 $18) 39... Ne6 (39... Qd7+ 40. Kg2 Nxb5 41. Qxg6+ Kf8 $18) 40. Bxe6
Qxe6+ (40... fxe6 41. b6 Qxb6 42. Qxg6+ Kf8 43. Ba3+ Nd6 44. Qxe6 Qxf2 45.
Bxd6+ Kg7 46. Be5+ Kf8 $18) 41. Qxe6 fxe6 42. Be5 Kf7 43. b6 Ke7 44. b7 (44. b7
Nf6 45. b8=Q g5 46. Qc7+ Nd7 47. Bd6+ Ke8 48. Qc8+ Kf7 49. Qxd7+ Kf6 50. Kg4
Kg6 51. Be5 Kh6 52. Qg7#) 1-0

