{[%mdl 8192] A48: 1 d4 Nf6 2 Nf3 g6: Torre, London and Colle Systems} 1. d4 Nf6
2. Nf3 g6 3. Bf4 Bg7 4. e3 O-O 5. Nc3 (5. c4 c5 6. Nc3 cxd4 7. exd4 (7. Nxd4
Nc6 8. Nxc6 bxc6 9. Be2 d6 10. O-O Qa5 11. Rc1 Be6 12. b3 Nd7 13. Qd2 g5 14.
Bg3 f5 15. Rfd1 Ne5 16. f4 Nf7 17. Bf3 Rac8 18. c5 g4 19. Be2 Qxc5 20. Bh4 Qa5
21. Bxe7 Rfe8 {Silva,F (2367)-Viterbo Ferreira,J (2324) Vila Nova de Gaia 2010
1-0 (86)}) 7... d5 8. Be2 Nc6 9. h3 dxc4 10. Bxc4 Na5 11. Be2 Be6 12. O-O Rc8
13. Re1 Nd5 14. Nxd5 Bxd5 15. Ne5 Bc4 16. Bxc4 Nxc4 17. Nxc4 Rxc4 18. Qb3 Rxd4
19. Be3 Rd7 {Zhukova,N (2395)-Cramling,P (2535) Belgrade 1998 1/2-1/2}) 5... d6
6. Be2 $146 (6. Bc4 c6 7. O-O b5 8. Bb3 a6 9. Ng5 Bb7 10. Qf3 Nbd7 11. Qh3 h6
12. Nf3 Nh5 13. Ne2 Ndf6 14. Qh4 Nxf4 15. Qxf4 g5 16. Nxg5 hxg5 17. Qxg5 Ne4
18. Qg4 c5 19. c3 Qc8 20. Qh4 Nd2 {Jovanovic,R (2200)-Jesenski,T (2287) Sombor
2004 0-1 (60)}) 6... Bf5 7. Nh4 Be6 8. Nf3 Nbd7 (8... Bf5 9. O-O $14) 9. h4 (9.
Ng5 Nb6 $14) 9... c5 10. Ng5 cxd4 11. exd4 {Black has a cramped position} Qa5 (
11... Qb6 12. Nxe6 fxe6 13. O-O $11) 12. h5 {White has a very active position}
(12. O-O Bf5 $14) 12... Nd5 $11 13. hxg6 $4 (13. Bd2 $142 {had to be tried to
avoid defeat} Bxd4 14. Nce4 $11) 13... Nxf4 $19 14. gxf7+ (14. gxh7+ Kh8 15.
Nxe6 fxe6 $19 (15... Nxe6 $6 16. Rh4 $17)) 14... Bxf7 15. Nxf7 Rxf7 (15... Kxf7
$6 16. g3 Nxe2 17. Qxe2 $17) 16. g3 (16. Bf3 {doesn't improve anything} e5 17.
Kf1 exd4 $19) 16... Nd5 (16... Ng2+ $142 {and Black has reached his goal} 17.
Kd2 Qg5+ 18. Kd3 Rxf2 $19) 17. Bc4 (17. Qd3 Nxc3 18. Qxc3 Qxc3+ 19. bxc3 Rc8
$19) 17... N7b6 18. Bb3 Kh8 $4 {simply marches past the door to victory} (18...
e6 $142 {secures the point} 19. Qd3 Nxc3 20. bxc3 d5 $19) 19. Qh5 $16 h6 (19...
Kg8 20. O-O-O (20. Bxd5 $6 Nxd5 21. Qxd5 Qxd5 22. Nxd5 Bxd4 $11) 20... e6 21.
Ne4 $16) 20. Qxf7 (20. Bxd5 $6 Nxd5 21. Qxd5 Qxd5 22. Nxd5 Bxd4 23. Rxh6+ Kg7
$14) 20... Nxc3 21. Kf1 {White loses the right to castle} (21. Qg6 $142 Ne4+
22. c3 $16) 21... Rf8 $4 {letting the wind out of his own sails} (21... Qb5+
$142 {this is the best way to fight back} 22. Kg2 Qc6+ 23. Qf3 Qxf3+ 24. Kxf3
Nca4 $11) 22. Qg6 $18 Qb5+ 23. Kg2 (23. Kg1 $5 {and White can already relax}
Ne2+ 24. Kg2 Qc6+ 25. d5 Qc5 (25... Nxd5 $143 26. Rxh6+ Kg8 27. Rah1 Rxf2+ 28.
Kxf2 Qb6+ 29. Ke1 Qg1+ 30. Rxg1 Nd4 31. Qe8+ Bf8 32. Rg6+ Kh7 33. Rh1+ Bh6 34.
Rhxh6#) 26. Rxh6+ Kg8 27. Qh7+ Kf7 $18) 23... Rxf2+ 24. Kxf2 $4 {overlooking
an easy win} (24. Kg1 $142 {it becomes clear that White will call all the shots
} d5 25. Rxh6+ (25. bxc3 $6 Qe2 26. Rh4 Rf6 $14) 25... Bxh6 26. Qxh6+ Kg8 27.
Kxf2 (27. bxc3 Qe2 28. Qg5+ Kf8 29. Qh6+ Ke8 $17) 27... Qe2+ 28. Kg1 $18) 24...
Qe2+ 25. Kg1 Bxd4# 0-1

