f6 17. Qg3 c5 18. a4 b6 19. Bd2 a6 20. b3 b5 21. axb5 axb5 22. Kh2 {Yu,Y (2675)
-Kryvoruchko,Y (2707) Dubai 2014 1-0 (60)}) 8. Nxb6 axb6 9. d4 Be6 $4 $146 (
9... Qe7 10. d5 Nb8 11. c4 Na6 12. Nc3 Ne8 13. Be3 f5 14. f4 fxe4 15. Nxe4 exf4
16. Bxf4 Bf5 17. Re1 Qd7 18. Ng5 Nc5 19. Re3 Nf6 20. b4 h6 21. bxc5 hxg5 22. c6
gxf4 23. cxd7 fxe3 24. Qe2 {Lupulescu,C (2598)-Nestorovic,N (2413) Bucharest
2010 1/2-1/2 (43)}) (9... exd4 $142 {was necessary} 10. Nxd4 Bd7 $11) 10. d5
$18 Bg4 11. dxc6 bxc6 12. h3 Bh5 (12... Be6 13. f4 $18) 13. Bg5 (13. c4 {
seems even better} Qe7 $18) 13... h6 14. Be3 Bg6 15. Nc3 d5 (15... Qe7 $18) 16.
exd5 cxd5 17. Nxd5 e4 18. Nxf6+ Qxf6 19. Qd4 Qe6 20. c4 (20. Qc3 {makes it
even easier for White} c5 $18) 20... c5 (20... Rfd8 {is not much help} 21. Qc3
$18) 21. Qc3 Rfd8 22. Rfd1 Re8 (22... Bh5 {doesn't change the outcome of the
game} 23. g4 Bg6 24. Bf4 $18) 23. a3 Rab8 (23... Rad8 {does not win a prize}
24. a4 $18) 24. Bf4 (24. Rd5 $5 {keeps an even firmer grip} Qc6 $18) 24... Rbd8
25. Be3 Qc6 $4 {there were better ways to keep up the pressure} (25... Rb8 26.
Rd5 f6 $18) 26. b4 $18 cxb4 (26... f6 {cannot change what is in store for White
} 27. bxc5 bxc5 28. Rxd8 Rxd8 29. a4 $18) 27. axb4 b5 (27... Qe6 {does not
help much} 28. Rxd8 Rxd8 29. Bf1 $18) 28. c5 Rc8 (28... f6 $18 {doesn't change
anything anymore}) 29. Rd6 (29. Bf1 $142 {seems even better} Red8 $18) 29...
Qc7 $4 (29... Qxd6 $142 $1 {and Black could well hope to play on} 30. Bd4 Qf8
$16) 30. Bf1 (30. Bf4 $142 {secures victory} Qb7 31. c6 $18) 30... Qxd6 $16 31.
Bxb5 (31. cxd6 $6 Rxc3 32. Bxb5 Rd8 $11) 31... Red8 32. Bf4 (32. Ba6 Qd7 33.
Kh2 Ra8 $18) 32... Qd4 (32... Qd5 $5 $16) 33. Qxd4 Rxd4 34. Ba6 Rcd8 $2 (34...
Ra8 $142 35. b5 Bf5 $16) 35. b5 $18 Rd1+ $6 {doesn't do very much to defend
the position} (35... Rb4 36. c6 Bf5 $18) 36. Rxd1 Rxd1+ 37. Kg2 Bf5 (37... e3 {
doesn't get the cat off the tree} 38. Bxe3 Rb1 39. c6 Be4+ 40. f3 Rb2+ 41. Bf2
Bxc6 42. bxc6 $18) 38. b6 e3 39. Bxe3 (39. Kf3 $142 {and White has triumphed}
exf2 40. Kxf2 $18) 39... Be4+ $16 40. f3 Bc6 41. Kf2 Ra1 $4 {strolling merrily
down the path to disaster} (41... Kf8 42. Bf4 Rb1 43. Bc4 $16) 42. Bc4 (42. Bb5
$142 $1 {and White wins} Ra2+ 43. Ke1 Bxf3 44. c6 $18) 42... Rb1 $16 43. Bf4
Rb2+ (43... Kf8 44. Bd2 $16) 44. Ke3 g5 (44... Rb4 45. Ba6 $16) 45. Bc7 (45.
Be5 Rb4 46. Bd3 Rb3 $16) 45... Rc2 (45... Rb4 $142 46. Bd3 Rb3 $16) 46. Bd3 $4
{White threatens to win material: Bd3xc2. with this move White loses his
