{[%mdl 8256] B90: Sicilian Najdorf: Unusual White 6th moves, 6 Be3 Ng4 and 6
Be3 e5} 1. e4 c5 (1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 $14) 2. Nf3 $14 d6 {Covers e5} 3.
d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 {Black is behind in developement. Black's piece can't move: f8}
Nf6 {Black threatens to win material: Nf6xe4} 5. Nc3 a6 {Black is behind in
developement. Black's piece can't move: f8} 6. Be3 e5 7. Nb3 Be7 8. f3 {
Consolidates g4} Be6 9. Qd2 Nbd7 10. O-O-O b5 11. g4 b4 {Black threatens to
win material: b4xc3} 12. Ne2 (12. Nd5 Bxd5 13. exd5 Nb6 $11) 12... a5 $15 13.
g5 Nh5 14. f4 (14. Kb1 $142 $5 $15 {is worth looking at}) 14... a4 $17 15. Nbd4
{[%cal Yf4f5] White intends f5} exd4 16. Nxd4 b3 $1 {and the rest is history}
17. Kb1 (17. axb3 axb3 18. cxb3 (18. Nxb3 Nc5 {Decoy Double attack}) 18... Nc5
{Decoy Double attack}) (17. cxb3 axb3 18. axb3 (18. Nxb3 Nc5 {Decoy Double
attack} (18... Rxa2 {Discovered attack})) 18... Nc5 {Decoy Double attack})
17... bxc2+ $4 {not a good decision, because now the opponent is right back in
the game} (17... bxa2+ $142 {would have given Black the upper hand} 18. Ka1 Bg4
$19) 18. Qxc2 $15 O-O (18... Rc8 19. Nc6 Qc7 20. Bb5 $11) 19. f5 {White gains
space} Ne5 $4 {weakening the position. A valuable piece} (19... Rc8 $142 {
was much better} 20. Qg2 Bc4 $15) 20. fxe6 $18 Bxg5 21. Bxg5 (21. exf7+ $5 Nxf7
(21... Rxf7 $4 22. Ne6 Qe8 23. Nxg5 $18 (23. Bxg5 $6 Qxe6 24. Be2 Nf4 $11)) 22.
Bxg5 Nxg5 $18) 21... Qxg5 $16 22. exf7+ Rxf7 23. Bc4 (23. Nf5 $5 a3 24. Be2 $16
) 23... Nxc4 $11 24. Qxc4 Qc5 25. Qxc5 dxc5 26. Ne6 {White threatens to win
material: Ne6xc5} Rc8 27. Rd5 {White threatens to win material: Rd5xh5. White
forks: c5+h5} Nf6 {Black threatens to win material: Nf6xd5. Black forks: d5+e4}
28. Rxc5 {White has a mate threat.} Re8 {Black threatens to win material:
Re8xe6} 29. Ng5 Nxe4 30. Nxe4 Rxe4 {A double rook endgame occured} 31. Rc8+ Rf8
32. Rxf8+ Kxf8 33. Rf1+ Ke7 34. Rf2 g5 35. Kc2 Ke6 36. Kd3 Ke5 37. Rf7 {
White threatens to win material: Rf7xh7} Rh4 {Black threatens to win material:
Rh4xh2} 38. Rf2 h5 39. Ke3 Rh3+ 40. Ke2 Ke4 41. Kf1 g4 {Black gets more space}
42. Kg2 Re3 43. Kf1 Rh3 44. Kg2 Re3 {Twofold repetition} 45. Kf1 Rh3 1/2-1/2

