Nf3 c5 4. cxd5 exd5 5. g3 Nc6 6. Bg2 Nf6 7. O-O Be7 8. Nc3 O-O 9. Bg5 c4 10.
Rc1 (10. b3 Qa5 11. Bd2 Bb4 12. Qe1 Qa6 13. e3 Re8 14. Ne5 Nxe5 15. dxe5 Rxe5
16. Nxd5 Nxd5 17. Bxb4 Bf5 18. Bc3 Nxc3 19. Qxc3 Rc5 20. b4 Rcc8 21. e4 Be6 22.
a4 Rd8 23. b5 Qb6 24. Rfd1 Rxd1+ {Haik,A (2445)-Miralles,G (2425) Marseille
1987 0-1 (38)}) 10... Re8 $146 (10... h6 11. Bf4 (11. Bxf6 Bxf6 12. e3 Be6 13.
b3 Na5 14. bxc4 (14. Ne5 Rc8 15. f4 Bxe5 16. fxe5 Qg5 17. Rf4 cxb3 18. axb3
Rfd8 19. Ne2 Qe7 20. Rf1 Qb4 21. Rxc8 Rxc8 22. Nf4 Rd8 23. Nxe6 fxe6 24. Qg4
Re8 25. Qg6 Qe7 26. e4 {1-0 (26) Lieb,H (2155)-Fischer,M (2163) Germany 2014})
14... Nxc4 15. Nd2 Rc8 16. Nxc4 Rxc4 17. Ne2 Qa5 18. Nf4 Rxc1 19. Qxc1 Qxa2 20.
Qa1 Qxa1 {1/2-1/2 (20) Headlong,T (2179)-Holland,J (2200) England 2011}) 11...
Bf5 12. Be5 Re8 13. Re1 Ne4 14. a3 Rc8 15. Qa4 Qd7 16. Qd1 Qe6 17. Bf4 Bf6 18.
Be3 Rcd8 19. Qa4 Bh3 20. Qb5 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 Rd7 22. Nxe4 Qxe4 23. Kg1 a6 24. Qa4
h5 25. b3 {Jancovic,P (2171)-Privara,I (2205) Slovakia 2015 1-0 (36)}) (10...
Be6 11. b3 cxb3 12. Qxb3 $11) 11. Ne5 Be6 12. f4 {White has a new backward
pawn: e2. Black has an active position} Ng4 (12... Qb6 13. e3 Qxb2 14. f5 $14)
13. Bxe7 (13. Nxg4 Bxg4 14. Bxd5 Rc8 $14) 13... Nxe7 $11 14. Qd2 Nf6 15. e3 Qa5
(15... Rb8 16. Bf3 $11) 16. b3 (16. e4 dxe4 17. Nxe4 Qxd2 18. Nxd2 Rad8 $14)
16... b5 17. bxc4 bxc4 18. h3 {Covers g4} h5 19. Qe2 Nf5 {Black threatens to
win material: Nf5xg3} 20. Qf2 {Black has an active position} (20. Qe1 $142 Nh6
21. e4 dxe4 22. Nxe4 Qxe1 23. Rfxe1 Nxe4 24. Bxe4 $14) 20... Rac8 $4 {gives
the opponent counterplay} (20... Nd6 $142 $11 {is the best option Black has})
21. g4 $16 hxg4 (21... Nd6 22. f5 Bd7 23. g5 $18) 22. hxg4 Nxe3 (22... Nd6 23.
f5 Bd7 $18) 23. Qxe3 $18 Bxg4 (23... Nxg4 24. Nxg4 Bxg4 25. Qg3 $18) 24. Qg3
Bf5 25. Qg5 Bd3 (25... Be4 26. Nxe4 Nxe4 27. Bxe4 dxe4 28. Nxf7 Qxg5+ 29. fxg5
$18) 26. Rf3 (26. Nxd3 {and White can already relax} cxd3 27. Nxd5 Nxd5 28.
Bxd5 Qb6 29. Rxc8 Rxc8 30. Bxf7+ Kf8 $18) 26... Nh7 $2 (26... Qa3 27. Rg3 Qxc1+
28. Kh2 Bg6 29. Nxg6 Re3 (29... fxg6 $4 30. Qxg6 Rc7 31. Nxd5 $18) 30. Nxd5
Nxd5 31. Ne7+ Kf8 32. Nxc8 g6 33. Qh6+ Ke8 34. Bxd5 Kd7 35. Qh3+ Re6 36. Bxe6+
fxe6 $18) 27. Qh5 Re7 (27... g6 {cannot undo what has already been done} 28.
Qh6 Bf5 29. Re3 $18) 28. Rh3 f6 (28... Rxe5 {a last effort to resist the
inevitable} 29. Qxe5 Qc7 30. Nxd5 Qxe5 31. fxe5 Rb8 $18) 29. Nxd3 g6 30. Bxd5+
Kh8 31. Qh4 cxd3 32. Qxf6+ Rg7 33. Rxh7+ $1 {Decoy: h7} (33. Rxh7+ Kxh7 34.
Qh4#) 1-0

