{[%mdl 8256] D02: 1 d4 d5 2 Nf3 sidelines, including 2...Nf6 3 g3 and 2...Nf6
3 Bf4} 1. d4 d5 2. Bf4 Nf6 3. Nf3 e6 4. e3 Bd6 5. Bg3 O-O 6. Bd3 Qe7 $146 (6...
Ne4 7. Bxe4 (7. Nbd2 f5 8. Ne5 Nxd2 9. Qxd2 Nd7 10. O-O-O Bxe5 11. Bxe5 Nxe5
12. dxe5 Bd7 13. f4 Qe7 14. g4 c5 15. gxf5 exf5 16. Bc4 dxc4 17. Qxd7 Qxd7 18.
Rxd7 Rf7 19. Rhd1 Re8 20. R1d5 b6 21. Kd2 g5 {Bodi,T (2185)-Salanki,E (2296)
Hungary 2010 1-0 (35)}) 7... dxe4 8. Nfd2 f5 9. O-O Nc6 10. Bxd6 cxd6 11. Nc3
d5 12. f4 b6 13. a3 Ba6 14. Rf2 Rc8 15. Nf1 Na5 16. Qe1 Qh4 17. g3 Qe7 18. Nd1
Rc7 19. b4 Nc4 20. a4 Bc8 21. c3 {Mason,J-Blackburne,J London 1883 1/2-1/2 (33)
}) (6... c5 7. c3 Qc7 (7... Nc6 8. O-O Bxg3 9. hxg3 Qd6 10. Bb5 Bd7 11. Nbd2
Nxd4 12. Nxd4 cxd4 13. Bxd7 dxe3 14. fxe3 Nxd7 15. g4 Qb6 {0-1 (15)
Ptaschinski,D (2220)-Boricsev,O (2415) Eger 1992}) 8. Ne5 Nbd7 9. f4 b6 10. Nd2
Bb7 11. Qf3 c4 12. Bc2 b5 13. Bh4 b4 14. Qh3 Ne4 15. O-O f5 16. Nxe4 dxe4 17.
Nxc4 bxc3 18. bxc3 Ba6 19. Nxd6 Qxd6 20. Rfc1 Rac8 21. Bb3 {Chernyshov,K (2544)
-Brinck Claussen,B (2359) Budapest 2006 1/2-1/2 (31)}) (6... b6 7. c3 c5 8.
Nbd2 Ba6 9. Bxa6 Nxa6 10. Qe2 Nc7 11. Ne5 h6 {1/2-1/2 (11) Slabek,A (2155)
-Sikora Gizynska,B (2225) Prague 1992}) 7. Ne5 b6 8. f4 c5 9. c3 c4 {Black
threatens to win material: c4xd3} 10. Bc2 Ne4 (10... Qc7 11. O-O $11) 11. Nd2 (
11. Bxe4 $142 dxe4 12. Nxc4 $14) 11... f6 $2 (11... Nxd2 12. Qxd2 Bb7 13. O-O
$11) 12. Nef3 $4 {Loses material. releasing the pressure on the opponent} (12.
Nxe4 $142 $5 fxe5 13. Nxd6 (13. dxe5 $6 Bxe5 14. fxe5 dxe4 $16) (13. fxe5 $6
Bxe5 14. dxe5 dxe4 $16) 13... Qxd6 14. fxe5 $18) 12... Bb7 (12... f5 $142 $5
$11 {is an interesting alternative}) 13. Nxe4 $16 dxe4 14. Nd2 f5 15. a4 $4 {
a transit from better to worse} (15. Nxc4 Nd7 $16) 15... Nd7 (15... Rc8 $142
$15 {would keep Black in the game}) 16. Nxc4 $16 Bc7 17. Bb3 Bd5 18. Nd2 Rad8
19. c4 Bb7 20. Qh5 {Black king safety dropped} Nf6 21. Qe2 {Black king safety
improved} Kh8 22. Bh4 Bc8 (22... h6 23. a5 $16) 23. h3 Qe8 (23... Qb4 24. O-O
$16) 24. g4 g6 (24... Ba6 25. O-O-O $16) 25. Bxf6+ Rxf6 26. g5 Rf8 (26... Rf7
27. O-O-O $16) 27. h4 $18 Rd7 28. h5 Rg7 29. hxg6 Rxg6 30. Qh5 Qf7 31. Qh2 $4 {
a transit from better to worse} (31. c5 $142 $18 {White had this great chance})
31... Rxg5 $11 32. O-O-O Rg7 33. Rdg1 Rxg1+ 34. Rxg1 Rg8 35. Rxg8+ Qxg8 36. Nf1
Bd6 37. d5 exd5 38. cxd5 Bb7 {Black threatens to win material: Bb7xd5} 39. Qd2
Qc8+ 40. Kb1 Kg8 (40... Qg8 41. Qe1 $11) 41. Qg2+ (41. Ng3 $5 $16) 41... Kh8
$11 42. Qd2 {Twofold repetition} Ba6 {Black threatens to win material: Ba6xf1}
(42... Kg8 43. Ng3 Ba6 44. Ka2 $16) 43. Qd4+ Kg8 44. Qf6 {White threatens to
win material: Qf6xd6} Qf8 {Black threatens to win material: Qf8xf6} 45. Qe6+ $4
{White is ruining his position} (45. Qg5+ $142 Kh8 46. Ng3 $11) 45... Kg7 (
45... Kh8 $142 {and Black wins} 46. Qd7 Bxf1 47. Qxa7 Bd3+ 48. Ka2 h5 $19) 46.
Ng3 $18 Bc8 47. Nh5+ (47. Nxf5+ $142 {and White takes home the point} Qxf5 48.
Qxd6 $18) 47... Kh8 $19 48. Qf6+ Qxf6 49. Nxf6 Be7 (49... Bc5 50. d6 Bxd6 51.
Kc2 $19) 50. Ne8 (50. Nh5 Bc5 $19) 50... Bc5 51. d6 (51. Kc2 $142 h5 52. Kd2
$19) 51... Bxe3 $4 {allows the opponent back into the game} (51... h5 $142 {
makes sure everything is clear} 52. Bc4 h4 $19) 52. Nf6 $17 Bxf4 53. d7 Bxd7 $1
{securing the lead.} 54. Nxd7 h5 (54... Kg7 $142 $5 $17) 55. Be6 $11 e3 {
Pushes the passed pawn} 56. Bc4 (56. Bxf5 $4 {capturing this pawn is a mistake}
e2 57. Ka2 Kg7 $19) 56... h4 57. Kc2 h3 {He broke from his leash} 58. Kd3 h2
59. Bd5 Be5 $4 {ignoring the path to victory} (59... Kg7 $142 $11 {would hold
out}) 60. Nxe5 $18 1-0

