Bb5+ Bd7 13. e5 $16) 11... Nxc4 (11... Bg7 12. b3 $11) 12. Qxc4 {Black has the
pair of bishops} (12. Nxc4 $5 {should be examined more closely} Bd7 13. b3 $14)
12... Bg7 $11 13. N2f3 O-O {Black castles and improves king safety} 14. Rb1 (
14. e4 Nb6 15. Qb4 a5 $11) 14... Bd7 (14... e5 15. Nb5 a6 16. Rd1 axb5 17. Qxd5
$17) 15. Bd2 (15. e4 $5 Nb6 16. Qe2 $15) 15... Rc8 $17 16. Qb3 b6 (16... Qb6
$142 $5 $17) 17. e4 $11 {White threatens to win material: e4xd5} Ne7 18. Bg5 {
Black has a cramped position} e5 {Black threatens to win material: e5xd4} 19.
Ne2 {White has an active position} (19. Nb5 $5 a6 20. Nd6 $11) 19... Be6 $15 {
Black threatens to win material: Be6xb3} 20. Qb4 Re8 (20... f6 21. Rfd1 Qe8 22.
Bd2 $15) 21. Rbd1 (21. Rfd1 Qc7 $15) 21... Qc7 22. Bxe7 Rxe7 23. Rc1 {White
threatens to win material: Rc1xc7} Qd8 24. Nc3 a5 {Black threatens to win
material: a5xb4} 25. Qb5 (25. Qa4 $15) 25... Bc4 (25... Rd7 $142 $17) 26. Qa4
$2 (26. Nd5 $142 {and White can hope to survive} Rec7 27. Qxb6 Bxd5 28. Rxc7
Qxc7 29. Qxc7 Rxc7 30. exd5 $11) 26... Bxf1 (26... b5 27. Nxb5 Bxf1 28. Rxf1
$19) 27. Rxf1 $17 Re6 28. Nd5 Bf8 29. b4 (29. Rd1 Bh6 $17) 29... axb4 30. axb4
Ra8 31. Qb5 f5 (31... Ra7 $142 $5 $17) 32. exf5 gxf5 33. Ne3 (33. Qc4 b5 34.
Qb3 Ra3 35. Qxa3 Qxd5 $11) 33... e4 {Black gets more space} (33... f4 $142 34.
Ng4 Qe8 $17) 34. Ne5 $2 (34. Qxf5 Qf6 35. Qg4+ Qg6 $15) 34... Qg5 $4 {allows
the opponent back into the game} (34... Qe8 35. Qxe8 Raxe8 36. Nd7 $19) 35.
N3c4 $4 (35. Qd5 $142 {was possible} Rae8 36. Nd7 $11) 35... f4 $19 36. Qd7 $2
