13. a3 Nc7 14. Nc3 Bxf3 15. Rxf3 Bd4+ 16. Kh1 Ne8 17. g4 Nhf6 18. Rg3 a6 19.
Rf1 Nd7 20. Bc1 Qd8 21. Rh3 Nc7 22. Qg2 Re8 {Erenska Barlo,H (2200)-Erneste,I 
(2300) Warsaw 1994 1-0 (34)}) 8... Nbd7 {Black has a cramped position. Black's
piece can't move: c8} 9. O-O a6 {Secures b5} 10. a4 b6 (10... Nh5 11. a5 $14)
11. Bd2 Bb7 12. Kh1 Kh8 13. Rae1 Kg8 14. b3 (14. Bc4 b5 15. axb5 axb5 16. Bxb5
Nb6 $16) 14... Rfe8 15. Nd1 (15. Bc4 e6 16. dxe6 fxe6 $16) 15... Rf8 (15... e6
$5 16. dxe6 Rxe6 $11 (16... fxe6 $143 17. Ng5 $14)) 16. Ne3 $14 Qb8 17. Qf2 Bc8
(17... h6 $5 $16) 18. e5 $1 {surprise!} dxe5 19. fxe5 Nxe5 20. Nxe5 Qxe5 21.
Nc4 (21. Nf5 Bxf5 22. Rxe5 Bxd3 23. Rxe7 Bxf1 $16) 21... Qc7 (21... Qxd5 $2 {
is nothing because of} 22. Nxb6 Qc6 23. Nxa8 $18) 22. Bf4 {White threatens to
win material: Bf4xc7} Qa7 {Black has a cramped position} 23. d6 {White
threatens to win material: d6xe7} e6 {White has a new passed pawn: d6. Black
has a new protected passed pawn: e6. Black has a cramped position} 24. Bg5 {
White threatens to win material: Bg5xf6} Nd7 {Blocks the pawn on d6} (24... Nd5
$5 $14 {is an interesting idea}) 25. Be7 $16 Bd4 26. Qf3 Bb7 27. Be4 (27. Qh3
Bg7 $16) 27... Bxe4 28. Rxe4 b5 29. Bxf8 (29. Nd2 Qb6 $16) 29... Rxf8 $14 30.
axb5 (30. Na3 $5 Bb2 31. axb5 Bxa3 32. Ra4 $14) 30... axb5 $11 31. Ne3 Qa6 32.
Ng4 $2 (32. Qg3 $142 $5 $11 {would allow White to play on}) 32... Qxd6 $17 33.
Nh6+ Kg7 34. Nxf7 (34. Rh4 f5 $17) 34... Qe7 35. Rf4 Nf6 (35... Bf6 $142 $5 36.
Rxf6 Nxf6 $17 (36... Qxf6 $6 37. Qxf6+ Nxf6 38. Nd6 $15)) 36. Ng5 $11 h6 37.
Ne4 g5 {Black threatens to win material: g5xf4} (37... Be5 $5 38. Nxf6 Bxf4 39.
Qxf4 Rxf6 $11) 38. Nxf6 $11 gxf4 39. Nh5+ {White forks: f4} Kf7 40. Nxf4 Ke8 $4
{the final mistake, not that it matters anymore} (40... Bg7 41. Nd5+ Ke8 42.
Nxe7 Rxf3 43. Rxf3 Kxe7 $18) 41. Qa8+ (41. Qc6+ $142 {and White can already
relax} Qd7 42. Qa8+ Qd8 43. Qxd8+ Kxd8 44. Nxe6+ Ke7 45. Nxf8 Bg7 46. Ng6+ Ke6
$18) 41... Kf7 (41... Kd7 {doesn't change anything anymore} 42. Qa7+ Kd6 43.
Qb6+ Kd7 44. Qb7+ Kd6 45. Qxe7+ Kxe7 46. Ng6+ Kd6 47. Rxf8 h5 $18) 42. Qf3 {
Twofold repetition} (42. Nxe6+ $142 {and White can celebrate victory} Bf6 43.
Nxf8 $18) 42... Qd6 $4 {not a good decision, because now the opponent is right
back in the game} (42... Ke8 43. Qc6+ Qd7 44. Qa8+ Qd8 45. Qxd8+ Kxd8 46. Nxe6+
Ke7 47. Nxf8 $18) 43. Qh5+ {White forks: h6} (43. Nxe6+ $142 {secures the point
} Kxe6 44. Qxf8 Qxf8 45. Rxf8 $18) 43... Ke7 $4 (43... Kg8 $142 {saving the
game} 44. Qg4+ Bg7 $11) 44. Ng6+ $18 (44. Ng6+ Kd7 45. Nxf8+ Kc7 46. b4 $18)
1-0

