{[%mdl 8192] B90: Sicilian Najdorf: Unusual White 6th moves, 6 Be3 Ng4 and 6
Be3 e5} 1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Qxd4 Nf6 (4... Nc6 5. Bb5 Bd7 6. Bxc6
Bxc6 7. Bg5 h6 8. Bh4 e5 9. Qe3 Qxh4 10. Nge2 Qd8 11. O-O-O Nf6 12. f4 Qb6 13.
Qf3 Be7 14. g4 exf4 15. Nxf4 O-O-O 16. Rhe1 Kb8 17. Re3 Qc5 18. Ncd5 Bxd5 19.
exd5 {Muzychuk,A (2566)-Ushenina,A (2501) Beijing 2013 0-1 (48)}) (4... a6 5.
Be3 Nf6 6. O-O-O Nc6 7. Qb6 Qxb6 8. Bxb6 g6 9. Nd5 Nxd5 10. exd5 Ne5 11. Ne2
Bh6+ 12. Kb1 Bf5 13. Ng3 Bd7 14. Be2 Bb5 15. Rhe1 Kd7 16. Bd4 f6 17. Bxe5 Bxe2
18. Bxf6 exf6 19. Nxe2 {Asadli,V (2287)-Gupta,A (2625) Nakhchivan 2015 1/2-1/2
(48)}) 5. Qd1 $146 (5. Bg5 Nfd7 6. O-O-O Nc6 7. Qd2 h6 8. Be3 g6 9. h4 Bg7 10.
f4 Nf6 11. Be2 Ng4 12. Bxg4 Bxg4 13. Nf3 Qa5 14. Kb1 Bxc3 15. bxc3 Be6 16. c4
Bxc4 17. c3 O-O-O 18. g4 e5 19. Qc2 exf4 {Bednar,J (2362)-Demeter,P (2297)
Bratislava 2004 1-0 (47)}) 5... a6 {Black has a cramped position. Black's
piece can't move: f8} 6. Bd3 e5 7. Nf3 {Black is behind in developement} Be7 8.
O-O O-O 9. Re1 h6 {Prevents intrusion on g5} 10. h3 {Secures g4} Be6 11. Bd2
Nbd7 12. Be3 b5 13. a3 {Black has a cramped position} Qc7 (13... Rc8 14. a4 b4
15. Ne2 $15) 14. Be2 {White has an active position} (14. Nh4 $5 $11 {is worth
looking at}) 14... Rfd8 15. Nd5 Bxd5 16. exd5 Nb6 17. Bxb6 Qxb6 18. b3 $2 (18.
Nd2 $142 $15 {and White hangs on}) 18... Ne4 $19 19. Rf1 Nc3 (19... Bf6 20. Nh2
Nc3 21. Qe1 $19) 20. Qd3 (20. Qe1 Qc5 21. b4 $19) 20... e4 $4 {Black threatens
to win material: e4xd3. Black forks: d3+f3. weakening the position} (20... Rac8
$142 {and the scales tip in favour of Black} 21. Nd2 f5 $19) 21. Qxc3 $15 {
White wins a piece} Bf6 22. Qe3 Qxe3 23. fxe3 exf3 24. Rae1 $4 (24. gxf3 $142 {
this is the best bet to save the position} Bxa1 25. Rxa1 $15) 24... fxe2 $19
25. Rxe2 Re8 (25... Rac8 {keeps an even firmer grip} 26. Kf2 $19) 26. Rf3 (26.
Kf2 {doesn't get the cat off the tree} Rac8 $19) 26... Re4 27. Rf4 Rae8 (27...
Re5 {might be the shorter path} 28. e4 $19) 28. Rxe4 Rxe4 29. Kf2 Bb2 30. c4 (
30. Kf3 {a fruitless try to alter the course of the game} f5 $19) 30... Bxa3
31. Kf3 Re8 32. Rc2 (32. cxb5 {does not save the day} axb5 33. Rd2 f5 $19)
32... bxc4 (32... Bc5 {and Black can already relax} 33. e4 bxc4 34. Rxc4 $19)
33. bxc4 (33. Rxc4 {is not much help} Bc5 34. e4 Rb8 $19) 33... Bc5 34. e4 f6
35. Ra2 Ra8 36. Kf4 Kf7 37. Kf5 (37. Ra5 {is no salvation} Kg6 $19) 37... g6+ (
37... a5 $5 {might be the shorter path} 38. Ra4 Rb8 39. Rxa5 g6+ 40. Kf4 $19)
38. Kf4 a5 39. h4 (39. Kf3 {does not help much} a4 40. Ke2 a3 $19) 39... Bb4 (
39... a4 $142 $5 {makes it even easier for Black} 40. Kf3 a3 41. Ke2 $19) 40.
g4 (40. Ke3 {hardly improves anything} a4 $19) 40... Rc8 41. g5 (41. h5 {
a fruitless try to alter the course of the game} Rxc4 42. Kf3 Rc3+ 43. Ke2 Rg3
$19) 41... hxg5+ 42. hxg5 fxg5+ 43. Kxg5 (43. Ke3 {is no salvation} Rxc4 44.
Kd3 Rc3+ 45. Kd4 Rg3 $19) 43... Rxc4 44. Rf2+ Kg7 45. e5 (45. Kf4 $19 {
desperation}) 45... dxe5 46. Rf6 (46. d6 {doesn't get the cat off the tree} a4
47. Rh2 Bxd6 48. Rh7+ Kxh7 49. Kf6 a3 50. Ke6 Rd4 51. Kd7 a2 52. Kc6 a1=Q 53.
Kb7 Qa4 54. Kc8 Rb4 55. Kd8 Rb8#) 46... Be7 47. d6 Bxf6# 0-1

